[[File:Tabaristan-EN.svg|link=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Tabaristan-EN.svg|thumb|250x250px|Map showing Daylam in western [[Tabaristan]]]]
'''Daylam''', also known in the plural form '''Daylaman''' (and variants such as '''Dailam''', '''Deylam''', and '''Deilam'''), was the name of a mountainous region of inland [[Gilan]], [[Iran]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=hvx9jq_2L3EC&lpg=PP1&pg=PA198&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=daylam&f=false|title=The Cambridge History of Iran|last=Frye|first=Richard Nelson|last2=Fisher|first2=William Bayne|last3=Madelung|first3=W.|date=1975-06-26|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=|isbn=9780521200936|location=|pages=|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=hvx9jq_2L3EC&dq=the+cambridge+history+of+iran+4&hl=da&source=gbs_navlinks_s&redir_esc=y|title=The Cambridge History of Iran|last=Frye|first=Richard Nelson|last2=Fisher|first2=William Bayne|last3=Bosworth|first3=C. E.|date=1975-06-26|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=|isbn=9780521200936|location=|pages=|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/buyids|title=BUYIDS - Encyclopaedia Iranica, Vol. IV, Fasc. 6|last=Tilman|first=Nagel|date=1990|website=www.iranicaonline.org|publisher=Routledge & Kegan Paul|location=London u.a.|pages=578–586|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-03-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=arELc_R1orcC&dq=The+Buwayhid+Dynasty+in+Iraq+334H/945+to+403H/1012:+Shaping+Institutions+for+the+future&hl=da&source=gbs_navlinks_s&redir_esc=y|title=The Buwayhid Dynasty in Iraq 334h., 945 to 403h., 1012: Shaping Institutions for the Future|last=Donohue|first=John J.|date=2003-01-01|publisher=BRILL|year=|isbn=9004128603|location=|pages=|language=en|access-date=3 February 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=I_9tAAAAMAAJ&q=The+Buwayhid+dynasty+of+Baghdad,+334/946-447/1055&dq=The+Buwayhid+dynasty+of+Baghdad,+334/946-447/1055&hl=da&sa=X&ei=L6nvUsiEGcfl4QT3noHQAQ&redir_esc=y|title=The Buwayhid Dynasty of Baghdad, 334/946-447/1055|last=Kabir|first=Mafizullah|date=1964-01-01|publisher=Iran Society|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=|language=en|access-date=3 February 2014}}</ref> It was so named for its inhabitants, known as the [[Daylamites]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/deylamites#pt2|title=DEYLAMITES – Encyclopaedia Iranica, Vol. BII, Fasc. 4|last=Wilferd Madelung|first=Wolfgang Felix,|date=1995|website=www.iranicaonline.org|pages=342–347|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-03-04}}</ref>

