{{short description|A seamount in the southern Atlantic in the Walvis Ridge}}

{{coord|23|14|40|S|8|16|20|E|display=title}}
The '''Ewing Seamount''' is a [[seamount]] in the southern [[Atlantic Ocean]], which lies on the [[Tropic of Capricorn]].<ref name=NatGeo>National Geographic Atlas of the World: Revised Sixth Edition, [[National Geographic Society]], 1992</ref><ref>[http://encarta.msn.com/map_701578938/Ewing_Seamount.html encarta.msn.com]</ref><ref>[http://earthref.org/cgi-bin/er.cgi?s=sc.cgi%3Fid%3DSMNT-232S-0083E earthref.org]</ref> Ewing is part of the [[Walvis Ridge]]<ref name=NatGeo/> having a mean depth of 4,500 metres and a summit depth of 700 metres.<ref>[http://seamounts.sdsc.edu/ Seamounts online]</ref>

